    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      AUTOFLOAT
      is a float with a special value literal, that indicates automatic choice of the value by the engine.
      BOOLEAN
      corresponds to lua type boolean.
      CONNECTIONS
      is a string with any combination of nesw.
      DIRECTION
      is essentially an integer but is represented by an enumerated list of integer constants for the four main directions.
      DIRECTION_NODIR
      provides an additional value NODIR.
      DIRECTION_RND
      has the additional value RANDOMDIR and is currently in use for the four-valued DIRECTION type only (by the stone st_mirror).
      DIRECTION8
      is an integer at the core with a specific set of value constants.
      DIRECTION8_NODIR
      provides an additional value NODIR.
      DIRECTION8_RND
      has the additional value RANDOMDIR and is currently unused.
      FLAGS
      is a type, that is essentially an integer, but the meaningful values are represented by summed (or rather bitwise or'd) predefined values.
      FLOAT
      corresponds to lua type float.
      FLOOR
      is a string containing the name of a floor.
      INTEGER
      corresponds to lua type integer.
      ITEM
      is a string containing the name of an item.
      KIND
      is a string containing the name of any kind.
      POSITION
      is either a Lua table with two numbers or an identifier of a positioned object or an instance of the Enigma API type po (which can be created by one of the previous).
      SELECTION
      is a lua table of strings representing kinds.
      STONE
      is a string containing the name of a stone.
      STRING
      corresponds to lua type string.
      TOKEN
      is a string that can serve as an identifier in lua.
